sql:
SELECT price
FROM orders
WHERE price > 1000;

SELECT trade_id 
FROM user_trades 
WHERE user_id = 1 AND trade_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'waves' refer to individual trades;
- 'sailors' refer to users;
- 'waves they've navigated' refers to the trade volume;
- 'average depth' refers to the average price of trades;
- 'position in the fleet' according to wave size refers to the trade rank based on total volume;
- 'depth of the sea based on wave size' refers to the cosine value of the metadata value for the wave size;
- Metadata key 'volume' indicates that the metadata value is related to the volume metric.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(type_id) 
FROM instrument_types 
WHERE type_id > 5;

SELECT trade_id
FROM trades
WHERE price > 5000;

external_knowledge:
- 'Voyage' metaphorically represents the action of trading;
- 'Vessels named after financial instruments' refers to specific financial instruments being traded;
- 'Seas of orders and trades' symbolizes the entire trading process;
- 'Waves of metadata' symbolizes additional contextual information (metadata) related to users and instruments;
- 'Mileposts' metaphorically signifies order IDs;
- 'Waves larger than a thousand gallons' symbolizes trade execution volumes greater than 1000 units;
- 'Mariners' refers to the users/traders;
- 'Names marked with the prefix 'user'' refers to usernames that start with 'user'.

- Navigators: Refers to users with the "trader" role; 
- Digital ocean of trading: Refers to the trading platform or market where users operate; 
- Ports of call: Refers to the email addresses of the users where they can be reached; 
- BTC-USDT-SPOT voyage: Refers to the specific trading instrument named "BTC-USDT-SPOT".

sql:
SELECT order_id, execution_price 
FROM order_executions 
WHERE execution_price > (SELECT AVG(execution_price) FROM order_executions);
